David Cameron will offer the public £4 billion of Lloyds Bank shares still held by the Government after Gordon Brown’s £20 billion panic bailout in 2008 . 
  Individuals will be allowed to buy up to £10,000 worth of shares . 
  The shares will be offered at a discount of at least 5 per cent on the market rate . 
  It would be the largest privatisation bonanza since the Thatcher era . 
 